much later in the marketing strategy process companies focus on sales and advertising only after all other factors of marketing have been determined this unit will teach you that marketing departments focus on a set of core principles most of which are summarized by the  ps product price place and promotion the  ps are also known as the marketing mix marketers use the marketing mix to determine the proper strategy for a product for example if an inventor comes to you with a new touchscreen technology how do you sell it you might first find a product in which the touchscreen would be useful such as a phone then determine a target price to maximize sales identify the best place to sell it eg online or in a store and finally decide how to promote it applying the  ps in this situation could give you the next iphone unit  time advisory completing this unit should take approximately  hours â˜Â Â  Â subunit   hours â˜ Â  Â subunit   hours â˜ Â  Â subunit   hours â˜ Â  Â subunit   hours â˜ Â  Â subunit   hours â˜ Â  Â subunit   hours â˜ Â  Â subunit   hours â˜ Â  Â unit  discussion forum  hours unit learning outcomes upon successful completion of this unit you will be able to define marketing and explain its function in society Â  explain the  ps of marketing Â  define advertising and sales and Â  describe ethical issues in marketing  marketing basics Â  reading principles of marketing â€œchapter  what is marketingâ€link principles of marketingÂ â€œchapter  what is marketingâ€Â pdf instructions read this chapter which defines and discusses the four components of marketing identifies the various institutions and entities that engage in marketing activities and emphasizes the importance of marketing in society please pay extra attention to the fundamental  ps of marketing and the important concept of value this chapter also outlines the marketing plan and introduces future chapters as they relate to the marketing plan structure reading this chapter taking notes and answering 